2003–2009: Early roles ===
In 2003, Hale first appeared on television as a contestant in the Fox reality show American Juniors.

On July 30, 2003, Hale finished in fourth place and part of a group of the same name formed with the top 5 finishers (Chauncey Matthews, Danielle White and Tori & Taylor Thompson) but the group disbanded in 2005, after their self-titled studio album's lackluster sales.

Later, Hale served as a correspondent in New Orleans and co-hosted with Ryan Seacrest in Times Square for Dick Clark's New Year's Rockin' Eve (2016–2021), making her the first millennial actress to co-host the Times Square segments.
Hale recorded two stand-alone Christmas songs "Mistletoe" and "You're Here", both released in 2014 and 2017, respectively.
In 2018, Hale was cast in The CW comedy-drama series Life Sentence as Stella Abbott, a woman who finds out that her terminal cancer is cured.
On March 11, 2019, Hale was cast as the lead role in Katy Keene, based on the Archie Comics character of the same name.
